    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#ferri1923"/>, n. <citedRange>10</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.330</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>031400</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#lazzarini1998"/>, p. <citedRange>312</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" n="a">
                    <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀριστ_"><seg part="I">Ἀριστ</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name>
                    <lb n="2"/>τῶ <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63982"><name nymRef="#Ζεῦξις">Ζεύ<supplied reason="lost">ξ</supplied>ιος</name></persName></persName>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" n="b"> 
                     <ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Eumenis"><name nymRef="#Εὐμενίς"><expan><abbr>Εὐμενί</abbr><ex>δων</ex></expan></name></persName>
                     </ab>
                 </div>
                 <div type="textpart" n="c">
                     <ab>
                         <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Zeus"><name nymRef="#Ζεύς">Ζηνός</name></persName>
                    </ab>
                 </div>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="a.2"><lem>Ζεύ<supplied reason="lost">ξ</supplied>ιος</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SEG 9">Ζεύ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ξιδ</supplied>ος</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Appartenant à Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> fils de Zeuxis.</p>
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied> des Euménides.</p> 
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autel</supplied>de Zeus.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Belonging to Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> son of Zeuxis.</p>
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of the Eumenides.</p>
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altar</supplied> of Zeus</p>            
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Appartenente ad Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> figlio di Zeuxis.</p>
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> delle Eumenidi.</p>
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altare</supplied> di Zeus.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The three inscription on this wall are probably belonging together, but were cut separately and are not related syntactically, a) giving the name of 
                    the whorshipper, b) and c) indicating the spaces devoted respectively to the Eumenides and to Zeus.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
